    <div class="row item active bg-yellow">
      <div class="wow slideInLeft col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
        <article class="step">
          <h2>First step: Install Ruby Version Manager (RVM)</h2>
          <p>
            Open your terminal and write this line:
          <span class="step__boxes step__boxes--code">\curl -L https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable</span>
            <br>
            Basically RVM helps you to manage the different versions of ruby
            <br>
            <br>
            Now, close your terminal
          </p>
          <p class="step__next" href="#carousel-example-generic" role="button" data-slide="next">
            Take the next step <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"></i>
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
      <div class="wow slideInRight col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
        <article class="step">
          <%= image_tag 'linux-ruby-step1.png', :class => 'step__image' %>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>


    <div class="row item bg-red">
      <div class="wow slideInLeft col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
        <article class="step">
          <h2>Second step: Check if everything goes well !</h2>
          <p>
            Open your terminal again and type
            <br>
            <span class="step__boxes step__boxes--code">type rvm | head -n 1</span>
            <br>
            You should see a message saying
            <br>
            <span class="step__boxes step__boxes--instructions">rvm is a function</span>
          </p>
          <p class="step__next" href="#carousel-example-generic" role="button" data-slide="next">
            Take the next step <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"></i>
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
      <div class="wow slideInRight col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
        <article class="step">
          <%= image_tag 'linux-ruby-step2.png', :class => 'step__image' %>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row item bg-green">
      <div class="wow slideInLeft col-lg-6 col-md-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
        <article class="step">
          <h2>Third step: Finally ! We will install Ruby !!!</h2>
          <p>
            To install ruby, run this command:
            <span class="step__boxes step__boxes--code">rvm use ruby --install --default</span>
            <br>
            It might ask you for your password
            <br>
            Once is good, type:
            <span class="step__boxes step__boxes--code">ruby -v</span>
            <br>
            If you get:
            <span class="step__boxes step__boxes--instructions">ruby 2.2.1 or +</span>
            <br>
            your computer speaks now ruby !
          </p>
          <% link_to "pry.html" , :class => 'step__next' do %>
            Install PRY <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"></i>
          <% end %>
        </article>
